% As a general rule, do not put math, special symbols or citations
% in the abstract or keywords.
\begin{abstract}
In this paper, we present a new dereverberation algorithm 
called Temporal Masking and Thresholding
(TMT) to enhance the temporal spectral of spectral features
for robust speech recognition under reverberant environments.
This algorithm is motivated by the precedence effects and
temporal masking of human auditory perception. 
This work is an improvement of our previous dereverberation
work called Suppression of Slowly-varying components and
the falling edge of the power envelope (SSF). In TMT
algorithm compared to SSF, we use a different mathematical
model to model the temporal masking and thresholding.
Speech recognition results show that TMT algorithm is 
superior to other algorithms such as LTLSS, VTS, or SSF
for reverberation.
\end{abstract}

% Note that keywords are not normally used for peerreview papers.
\begin{IEEEkeywords}
Robust speech recognition, speech enhancement, reverberation,
temporal masking, precedence effect
\end{IEEEkeywords}

