\section{Structure of POC processing}
\label{sec:structure_of_TMT_processing}

Figure \ref{fig:TMT_block_diagram} shows the entire structure of 
TMT processing. In the discussion below, we assume that the
sampling rate of the speech signal is 16 {\it kHz}, however this algorithm
may be applied for other sampling rates as well.
%
%
TODO(chanwcom) % Obtain the optimal frame length by experiments.
Speech is segmented into 100 ms frames with 10 ms intervals between
adjacent frames. A Hamming window is applied for each frame, and
Short-time Fourier Transform (STFT) is performed. 
Spectral power in 40 analysis bands is obtained. Temporal masking
and thresholding are performed for each channel, and the speech
spectrum is reshaped based on these processing. Finally, the
output speech is resynthesized using the IFFT and the OverLap Addition
(OLA) method. The following subsections describe each stage in more detail.

\begin{figure}
    \begin{center}
    {\includegraphics[width=65mm]{../figures/draw_filter_bank_responses.eps}}
    \caption {
      The shape of the gammatone filterbank frequency responses whose
      amplitudes are normalized using \eqref{eq:unity_constraint}.
    	}
    	\label{fig:TMT_block_diagram}
    \end{center} \vspace{-5mm}
\end{figure}


